="de" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete"><p>
            <milestone unit="line" n="1"/>Im 26. Jahr des Aurelius Commodus Antoninus Caes[ar], des Herren, am 21. 
            [Tho]th.
            <milestone unit="line" n="2" rend="break"/>Pa[kys]is, Sohn des Stotoêtis des Jüngeren, des Sohnes des Stoto[ê]ti[s], 
            Priester, stellte seinen Sohn Hôros von der Mutter Pha[u]ês aus dem [Hêr]akleidês-Bezirk des 
            Arsinoïtês vor und beantragte, ihm zu gestatten, seinen Sohn zu beschneiden, 
            <milestone unit="line" n="5"/>weil er die Nachweise seiner Abstammung dem <term target="diadechomai">die Strategie stellvertretend 
                ausübenden</term> <term target="basilikosgrammateus">Königlichen 
                    (Schreiber)</term> des <app><lem><seg cert="low" part="N">Gaues</seg></lem><wit><bibl default="NO"/></wit></app>, 
            vorgelegt hatte, und <app type="BGU"><lem>&lt;übergab&gt;</lem><wit><bibl default="NO">BL I, S. 16</bibl></wit></app> den über ihn 
            geschriebene Brief. <milestone unit="line" n="8"/>Iulianus befragte die 
            <term lang="la" target="hierogrammateus"><foreign lang="la">hi[er]ogramm[at]eis</foreign></term>, ob der Junge ein 
            Kennzeichen habe. <milestone unit="line" n="9"/>Als sie sagten, daß er ohne Kennzeichen sei, zeichnete Salvius 
            Iulianus, der <term target="archiereus">Oberpriester</term> und <term target="hoepitonhieron">Zuständige für 
                die Heiligtümer</term>, den Brief gegen und ordnete an, 
            den Jungen gemäß der Gewohnheit zu beschneiden.
        </p></div><div n="tran.9124" type="translation" lang="en" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete"><p>
            <milestone unit="line" n="1"/>Year 26 of Aurelius Commodus Antoninus Caesar, the lord, [Tho]th 21.
            <milestone unit="line" n="2" rend="break"/>Pa[kys]is, son of Stotoetis the younger, the son of Stotoetis, priest, 
            having presented my own son Horos from his mother Pha[u]es from the Herakleides division of 
            the Arsinoite nome, requesting that permission be given to him that his son should be 
            circumcised <milestone unit="line" n="5"/>because he has produced certificates of birth to the <term target="basilikosgrammateus">royal 
                (scribe)</term> of the nome, who is <term target="diadechomai">administering 
                    the office of the strategos</term>, and <app type="BGU"><lem>&lt;having 
                        submitted&gt;</lem><wit><bibl default="NO">BL I 16</bibl></wit></app> a letter written concerning him, 
            <milestone unit="line" n="8"/>Ioulianos enquired of the <term target="hierogrammateus">keepers of the sacred 
                records</term>, whether the boy has any blemish. Upon their 
            saying that he is without a blemish Salvius Ioulianos, 
            <term target="archiereus">high-priest</term> and <term target="hoepitonhieron">minister for the temple 
                administration</term>, by appending his signature to the 
            letter gave permission for the boy to be circumcised in accordance with custom.
        </p></div></body></text></TEI.2>